Former presidential aide, Reno Omokri has concluded plan to stage protest in Paris the capital of France on Tuesday to ‘harass’ President Muhammadu Buhari back to Nigeria. Reno, who initiated a protest against the president during his medical trip to London recently, has urged Nigerians in Paris to convene at at the Temporary Exhibition Centre, in front of the Eiffel Tower on Tuesday for a peaceful protest. The former President, Goodluck Jonathan’s aide, earlier conducted a poll on his Facebook page soliciting the idea of Nigerians particularly the youths to ascertain whether to harass or allow the president in France. DAILY POST correspondent who monitor the poll, observed that he concluded to embark on the protest after majority of his supporters opted in for the #harassBuhariOutOfParis. Reno made his decision known in a post on his official Facebook page. The post reads, “Do you love Nigeria? Are you based in Paris? Join us for the #HarassBuhariOutOfParis peaceful protest tomorrow, 12 noon, Paris Time, at the Temporary Exhibition Centre, in front of the Eiffel Tower. “Muhammadu Buhari can’t be globetrotting, while Nigeria is drifting. Go back and fix Nigeria! “Please do this for the love of Nigeria”. Ejike Mbaka: “Buhari wants to set Nigeria ablaze”- Omokri reacts to alleged arrest 